mestic bank in a foreign currency.","pos":[50968,51228]},{"pos":[51265,51285],"content":"Electronic reporting","linkify":"Electronic reporting","nodes":[{"content":"Electronic reporting","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[51289,51304]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[51583,51604]},{"content":"Configure ER reports to insert data, in several formats, from Document Management storage into electronic messages that are generated.","pos":[52963,53097]},{"content":"ER reports can insert data into electronic messages that are generated from the Document Management storage.","pos":[53257,53365]},{"content":"Therefore, the attachments of a business document can be added to electronic messages that are generated for that document, in accordance with the legal requirements.","pos":[53366,53532]},{"content":"Currently, these attachments can be added in MIME format to an XML message that is generated.","pos":[53533,53626]},{"content":"Alternatively, the attachments can be added in Base64 format to a binary message that is generated.","pos":[53627,53726]},{"content":"Configure ER reports to generate electronic documents in Excel, Microsoft Word, or PDF format.","pos":[53800,53894]},{"content":"One configuration enables ER reports to generate electronic documents in three different formats: OpenXML worksheet (Excel), Word, and XML Forms Data Format (XFDF) (PDF).","pos":[54094,54264]},{"content":"Users can select a format by adding a format template to an ER report as an Excel, Word, or PDF document.","pos":[54265,54370]},{"content":"Configure ER reports to insert data into page headers and footers of electronic documents that are generated in OpenXML worksheet format, and to control page breaks.","pos":[54637,54802]},{"content":"ER reports can enter business data into page headers and footers, and also control where page breaks occur.","pos":[54931,55038]},{"content":"Therefore, the reports can support static top and bottom sections for pages of the electronic documents that are generated.","pos":[55039,55162]},{"content":"They can also support specific paging of those documents, so that they comply with legal requirements.","pos":[55163,55265]},{"content":"Configure the destination of ER reports so that the output is sent as email, and so that business data and ER logic (expressions) can be used to specify, at run time, the email address to use.","pos":[55474,55666]},{"content":"Previously, when you configured an ER destination, the email address of the output’s recipient could be defined at design time.","pos":[55768,55895]},{"content":"You can now configure an expression in the ER format.","pos":[55896,55949]},{"content":"This expression can then be selected in a destination as the source of the email address for each format configuration and each output component (folder or file) separately.","pos":[55950,56123]},{"content":"Therefore, when an ER report is running, each file that is generated can be mailed to a different recipient, and the email address can be defined based on ER logic and business data.","pos":[56124,56306]},{"content":"Configure the destination of ER reports so that the output is sent to the Microsoft SharePoint folder as either a new named file or a new version of the existing file, and so that business data can be used in the Microsoft Power BI framework as either a data set or a report.","pos":[56311,56586]},{"content":"When you configure ER reports, you can now easily (without coding) prepare the requested business data so that it can be used by the Power BI framework.","pos":[56605,56757]},{"content":"When you run those ER reports, you can provide the Power BI framework with appropriate business data and/or Excel reports that are already available.","pos":[56758,56907]},{"content":"If you schedule the report runs in recurrent mode, you can establish the scheduled push of business data from Dynamics 365 for Operations to Power BI to support the update schedule of Power BI–based reports.","pos":[56908,57115]},{"content":"Configure ER reports to use the part of the electronic document that has already been generated as a data source to generate the rest of that document.","pos":[57148,57299]},{"content":"You can configure ER reports that create the output in text format to do the document’s line counting.","pos":[57442,57544]},{"content":"This information can then be used in other parts of the document to create lines that include summary details.","pos":[57545,57655]},{"content":"The summary information (totals and numbers) can be computed and printed to the electronic documents that are generated, without requiring additional transformations of the data.","pos":[57656,57834]},{"content":"Therefore, this feature improves the performance of report execution and helps keep the future maintenance of the configured ER format easier.","pos":[57835,57977]},{"content":"Configure ER reports to specify the file name extension for electronic documents that are generated in text format.","pos":[57985,58100]},{"content":"You can configure ER reports to create the output in text format, so that it can be saved as a file that has a specific extension.","pos":[58279,58409]},{"content":"In addition to the default .txt extension, you can configure extensions such as .csv and .prn, in accordance with the format specification.","pos":[58410,58549]},{"content":"Create new ER reports that are based on a specific version of an ER model.","pos":[58822,58896]},{"content":"Previously, when you created a new ER format, only the most recent version of the selected ER model could be used as the format’s data source location.","pos":[59116,59267]},{"content":"You can now select any available version of the selected ER model.","pos":[59268,59334]},{"content":"This feature lets you maintain ER reports for the current year and design a new version of the ER model for the next year in parallel.","pos":[59335,59469]},{"content":"Search data sources and formats/models by text or selected artifact in one click.","pos":[59659,59740]},{"content":"Proactively resolve rebase conflicts, and resolve conflicts between configurations.","pos":[59741,59824]},{"content":"Configure ER reports to create multiple validation messages for errors that are discovered until report execution is stopped.","pos":[59825,59950]},{"content":"Several user experience (UX) improvements in the ER framework help users work with ER more efficiently and easily.","pos":[59953,60067]},{"pos":[60496,60542],"content":"Show the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ER<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> workspace on Power BI reports.","source":"Show the **ER** workspace on Power BI reports."},{"pos":[60790,60922],"content":"Users can configure the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ER workspace<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page so that it includes new menu items and live tiles that run the Power BI–based reports.","source":"Users can configure the **ER workspace** page so that it includes new menu items and live tiles that run the Power BI–based reports."},{"pos":[61335,61342],"content":"Payroll","linkify":"Payroll","nodes":[{"content":"Payroll","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[61387,61402]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[61412,61433]},{"content":"Configure pay records and process payroll by using functionality that is equivalent to the functionality of the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Payroll<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> module in Microsoft Dynamics AX 2012 R3.","pos":[61483,61660],"source":"Configure pay records and process payroll by using functionality that is equivalent to the functionality of the <strong>Payroll</strong> module in Microsoft Dynamics AX 2012 R3."},{"content":"You can now configure and process US payroll by using a feature set that is equivalent to the feature set in AX 2012 R3.","pos":[61670,61790]},{"content":"You can configure pay cycles and pay periods, work cycles and work periods, earning codes and earning code groups, schedules, leave types, and benefit accrual plans.","pos":[61800,61965]},{"content":"You can also set up mandatory deductions for both benefits and taxes, and record payroll information for positions and workers for reporting and analysis purposes.","pos":[61975,62138]},{"content":"You can also set up and manage deductions for garnishments and tax levies, and for any associated administrative fees.","pos":[62148,62266]},{"content":"Monitor and process your pay period process by using the new <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Payroll management<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> workspace.","pos":[62311,62418],"source":"Monitor and process your pay period process by using the new <strong>Payroll management</strong> workspace."},{"content":"You can now easily monitor your payroll processing.","pos":[62428,62479]},{"content":"At a glance, payroll administrators can see earning and pay statements that require their attention, so that the pay run will be complete and accurate.","pos":[62480,62631]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Payroll management<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> workspace lets users monitor and run end-to-end processes from a single workspace.","pos":[62632,62754],"source":" The <strong>Payroll management</strong> workspace lets users monitor and run end-to-end processes from a single workspace."},{"content":"Generate positive pay files for payroll checks.","pos":[62787,62834]},{"content":"There is a new extension to Cash and bank management’s positive pay functionality for payroll payments.","pos":[62844,62947]},{"content":"Separate menu items have been added throughout the core process to enable isolated configuration that is specific to payroll.","pos":[62948,63073]},{"content":"Functionality is identical to the core positive pay feature that was released in Microsoft Dynamics AX application version 7.0.1 (May 2016).","pos":[63074,63214]},{"content":"Because of this extension, payroll data is completely isolated from the rest of your positive pay transactions.","pos":[63215,63326]},{"content":"This isolation helps guarantee that only payroll users can access and see data that is related to payroll.","pos":[63327,63433]},{"content":"Import earnings statement lines from an external source by using the new Earning Statement Line data entity.","pos":[63467,63575]},{"content":"An important new data entity enables integration with external time and earning calculation systems.","pos":[63585,63685]},{"content":"The data entity imports earnings statement lines and performs all the same default logic that the user entered directly on the earning statement.","pos":[63686,63831]},{"content":"After import, the lines are automatically associated with the appropriate earnings statement document.","pos":[63832,63934]},{"content":"If an appropriate earnings statement document doesn't exist, a document is created automatically.","pos":[63935,64032]},{"pos":[64066,64089],"content":"Planning and scheduling","linkify":"Planning and scheduling","nodes":[{"content":"Planning and scheduling","pos":[0,23]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[64092,64107]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[64307,64328]},{"content":"Set default order settings for sales and purchases, based on any active product dimension on the product master.","pos":[65374,65486]},{"content":"Therefore, you can define default order settings for the stock keeping unit (SKU) or a partial SKU.","pos":[65487,65586]},{"content":"You can specify default order settings that apply to a product dimension or a combination of product dimensions.","pos":[65589,65701]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Example<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> You sell a product that is named Polo T-shirt.","pos":[65702,65760],"source":"**Example** You sell a product that is named Polo T-shirt."},{"content":"This product is available in two colors: Green and Blue.","pos":[65761,65817]},{"content":"It’s also available in two sizes: Small and Medium.","pos":[65818,65869]},{"content":"Color and Size are active product dimensions for Polo T-shirt.","pos":[65870,65932]},{"content":"You can block purchases of all green Polo T-shirts, regardless of their size.","pos":[65933,66010]},{"pos":[66017,66036],"content":"Product master data","linkify":"Product master data","nodes":[{"content":"Product master data","pos":[0,19]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[66081,66096]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[66106,66127]},{"content":"Set up all default order settings and site-specific order settings at the same time, from one page.","pos":[66177,66276]},{"content":"This feature provides a better overview of item settings.","pos":[66286,66343]},{"content":"Create a nomenclature for product variant numbers.","pos":[66377,66427]},{"content":"You can include elements such as product dimensions, attributes, and characters in your product variant numbers.","pos":[66437,66549]},{"content":"When you create a sales order or a purchase order, you can quickly find the specific product variant.","pos":[66550,66651]},{"content":"Search for products and product variants in sales and purchase scenarios.","pos":[66684,66757]},{"content":"When you create a sales line or a purchase line, you can search for products by using product dimensions and any product numbers except Global Trade Item Numbers (GTINs) and barcodes.","pos":[66767,66950]},{"content":"This search is a full-text search that replaces the existing “Begins with” search that is used in the sales and purchase lookup list.","pos":[66951,67084]},{"content":"This feature lets you find groups of products that have similar properties or a single product that has unique characteristics.","pos":[67085,67212]},{"content":"To turn on this feature, select the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Enable lookup for product search<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> parameter on the <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Search parameters<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> page.","pos":[67213,67356],"source":" To turn on this feature, select the <strong>Enable lookup for product search</strong> parameter on the <strong>Search parameters</strong> page."},{"content":"Specify the product variant directly when you create a sales or purchase transaction.","pos":[67390,67475]},{"content":"Alternatively, you can select in a list of valid dimension combinations.","pos":[67476,67548]},{"content":"This feature is a productivity enhancement.","pos":[67558,67601]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Example<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> You sell a product that is named Polo T-shirt.","pos":[67602,67673],"source":"<strong>Example</strong> You sell a product that is named Polo T-shirt."},{"content":"This product is available in two colors: Green and Blue.","pos":[67674,67730]},{"content":"It’s also available in two sizes: Small and Medium.","pos":[67731,67782]},{"content":"Color and Size are active product dimensions for Polo T-shirt.","pos":[67783,67845]},{"content":"When you enter a sales line for Polo T-shirt that has color Green and size Small, you don’t have to enter data in the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Item number<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Color<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p3\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Size<ept id=\"p3\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> fields.","pos":[67846,68051],"source":" When you enter a sales line for Polo T-shirt that has color Green and size Small, you don’t have to enter data in the <strong>Item number</strong>, <strong>Color</strong>, and <strong>Size</strong> fields."},{"content":"You can create the line by following one of these steps:","pos":[68052,68108],"source":" You can create the line by following one of these steps:\n"},{"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Item number<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> field, enter the product variant number, the value of a color, or the size.","pos":[68118,68229],"source":"In the <strong>Item number</strong> field, enter the product variant number, the value of a color, or the size."},{"content":"In the lookup, find the specific variant that you want to sell, and create the sales line.","pos":[68230,68320]},{"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Item number<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> field, enter the item number.","pos":[68330,68395],"source":"In the <strong>Item number</strong> field, enter the item number."},{"content":"Go to any product dimension field.","pos":[68396,68430]},{"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Product dimension<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> lookup, you will see all the released dimension combinations that apply to Polo T-shirt.","pos":[68431,68561],"source":" In the <strong>Product dimension</strong> lookup, you will see all the released dimension combinations that apply to Polo T-shirt."},{"content":"In one step, you can select the product variant that you want to sell.","pos":[68562,68632]},{"content":"Specify whether product numbers appear on transactional pages.","pos":[68676,68738]},{"content":"The transactional pages, such as sales orders and purchase orders, show only the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Item number<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Product name<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> fields.","pos":[68748,68899],"source":"The transactional pages, such as sales orders and purchase orders, show only the <strong>Item number</strong> and <strong>Product name</strong> fields."},{"content":"To see the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Product number<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> field, select the <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Show product numbers on forms<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> parameter under <bpt id=\"p3\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Product information management parameters<ept id=\"p3\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept>.","pos":[68900,69083],"source":" To see the <strong>Product number</strong> field, select the <strong>Show product numbers on forms</strong> parameter under <strong>