content":"Extensibility","pos":[0,13]}]},{"content":"Commerce runtime projects are now sealed from Retail SDK.","pos":[78955,79012]},{"content":"Easier deployment and servicing through componentized Microsoft component packages and ISV packages for the POS, Retail Server, Databases, Payment and Hardware stations.","pos":[79017,79186]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[79190,79205]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[79320,79341]},{"content":"CRT/Retail Server: Retailers or ISVs can extend the CRT through extension hooks.","pos":[79872,79952]},{"content":"Inline code changes are not supported anymore.","pos":[79953,79999]},{"content":"To enable continuous integration and continuous deployment, inline code changes should be completely avoided.","pos":[80002,80111]},{"content":"Also, to support easy uptake of hotfix without any code merge and deployment for CRT components.","pos":[80112,80208]},{"pos":[80216,80252],"content":"Personalized product recommendations","linkify":"Personalized product recommendations","nodes":[{"content":"Personalized product recommendations","pos":[0,36]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[80256,80271]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[80537,80558]},{"content":"View personalized product recommendations at multiple touchpoints on point-of-sale (POS) to determine what a customer might be interested in based on their purchase history, items in their wish list, and items that other customers purchased online and in brick-and-mortar stores","pos":[81764,82042]},{"content":"For retailers with large catalogs, personalized recommendations help the customer with product discovery and empower store associates with intelligent clienteling.","pos":[82045,82208]},{"content":"By showcasing products targeted to a customer’s interests and buying habits, product recommendations can help retailers with upsell and can enhance customer retention.","pos":[82209,82376]},{"content":"In Microsoft Dynamics 365 for Retail, product recommendations are powered by cognitive services and Microsoft Azure machine learning.","pos":[82377,82510]},{"pos":[82518,82535],"content":"POS task recorder","linkify":"POS task recorder","nodes":[{"content":"POS task recorder","pos":[0,17]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[82539,82554]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[82750,82771]},{"content":"Retailers can use POS task recorder to produce training materials, Business process modeler (BPM) diagrams, and generate Help content to enhance productivity and do better analysis and design of applications.","pos":[83371,83579]},{"content":"To enable continuous integration and continuous deployment inline changes should be completely avoided.","pos":[83582,83685]},{"content":"Also, to support easy uptake of hotfix without any code merge and deployment for CRT components.","pos":[83686,83782]},{"content":"Real time help in POS.","pos":[83787,83809]},{"content":"Cashier/Manager can get real time help from POS on business process without switching context.","pos":[83998,84092]},{"pos":[84206,84269],"content":"Store system: Providing a seamless on-premises store experience","linkify":"Store system: Providing a seamless on-premises store experience","nodes":[{"content":"Store system: Providing a seamless on-premises store experience","pos":[0,63]}]},{"content":"Store system is a deployment choice for retailers that helps drive a set of store operations, whether in an on-premises store, Microsoft public cloud, or the customer’s own private cloud.","pos":[84271,84458]},{"content":"For this release, the scope is in-store only.","pos":[84459,84504]},{"content":"To better support environments that have slow and unreliable network connectivity, we must provide an option for retailers to deploy the channel database and Retail Server in the store.","pos":[84505,84690]},{"content":"They can then continue to run their core business scenarios even when there is no connectivity to headquarters (HQ).","pos":[84691,84807]},{"content":"Based on the various data points, which included engineering team discussions, customer survey results, and competitor analysis, we have identified the following solution scope as the ideal fit for our target customers:","pos":[84808,85027]},{"content":"A self-service package is available for Store system.","pos":[85033,85086]},{"content":"The default installation is a one-box deployment, but custom deployment is allowed.","pos":[85091,85174]},{"content":"Enable easy deployment/self-servicing.","pos":[85179,85217]},{"content":"Retail Server and the store database are in the store, together with the Async Client service.","pos":[85222,85316]},{"content":"Retail Server in the store communicates directly with Application Object Server (AOS) in HQ for Store system.","pos":[85321,85430]},{"content":"Support cross-terminal scenarios where there is no HQ connectivity.","pos":[85435,85502]},{"content":"Retail Modern POS and Cloud POS always communicate with Retail Server in the store.","pos":[85507,85590]},{"content":"Support Retail Modern POS and Cloud POS where there is no HQ connectivity.","pos":[85595,85669]},{"content":"Support a Retail Modern POS–specific offline database (isolated to each Retail Modern POS instance) where there is no HQ connectivity.","pos":[85674,85808]},{"content":"Authentication is based on service-to-service only for Store system.","pos":[85813,85881]},{"content":"Real-time Service calls aren’t supported if there is no Internet connectivity.","pos":[85886,85964]},{"content":"Direct database connectivity of Retail Modern POS to the channel database isn’t supported.","pos":[85969,86059]},{"content":"Enable telemetry/monitoring.","pos":[86064,86092]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[86096,86111]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[86248,86269]},{"content":"A retailer downloads the Store system self-service installer from the channel database page in Dynamics AX HQ and downloads the configuration file.","pos":[86616,86763]},{"content":"The retailer can seamlessly download the self-service package.","pos":[86768,86830]},{"content":"A retailer installs Store system by using the self-service installer.","pos":[86876,86945]},{"content":"The retailer can install Store system by using the self-service package.","pos":[87028,87100]},{"content":"The IT manager configures Store system in Dynamics 365 for Operations (channel database, channel profile, store, and deployable package).","pos":[87136,87273]},{"content":"The IT manager can configure Store system easily and efficiently.","pos":[87288,87353]},{"content":"A retailer operates Retail Modern POS in the on-premises store and can do real-time operations, such as issue gift cards, when there is connectivity.","pos":[87396,87545]},{"content":"The retailer can perform real-time actions from Store system when there is connectivity.","pos":[87548,87636]},{"content":"A retailer can sync data from the on-premises Store system to HQ whenever there is connectivity.","pos":[87656,87752]},{"content":"The retailer can sync to and from Store system when there is connectivity.","pos":[87808,87882]},{"content":"A retailer can have secure communication between the on-premises Store system and HQ.","pos":[87916,88001]},{"content":"The retailer can communicate from Store system securely when there is connectivity.","pos":[88068,88151]},{"content":"The IT manager and Microsoft Operations can monitor and report on the on-premises Store system (diagnostics and reporting changes).","pos":[88176,88307]},{"content":"The IT manager and Microsoft Operations can monitor Store system securely and troubleshoot efficiently.","pos":[88328,88431]},{"pos":[88439,88491],"content":"Universal Windows Platform app for Retail Modern POS","linkify":"Universal Windows Platform app for Retail Modern POS","nodes":[{"content":"Universal Windows Platform app for Retail Modern POS","pos":[0,52]}]},{"content":"Currently, Retail Modern POS is available only as a Windows 8.1 application for desktop computers and tablets, and as Cloud POS for desktop or tablet browsers.","pos":[88493,88652]},{"content":"In this release, Retail Moderns POS is being converted to a Universal Windows Platform (UWP) app.","pos":[88653,88750]},{"content":"This change will enable Retail Modern POS to run on any Windows 10 device (desktop, tablet, or phone) and even switch between views for Continuum-enabled devices.","pos":[88751,88913]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[88917,88932]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[88985,89006]},{"content":"Enable important POS functionality for small-form-factor devices.","pos":[89273,89338]},{"content":"Retail POS functionality is available for phones and other small-form-factor devices that run Windows 10.","pos":[89341,89446]},{"pos":[89453,89476],"content":"Supply chain management","linkify":"Supply chain management","nodes":[{"content":"Supply chain management","pos":[0,23]}]},{"pos":[89481,89502],"content":"Consignment inventory","linkify":"Consignment inventory","nodes":[{"content":"Consignment inventory","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[89506,89521]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[89683,89704]},{"content":"As a vendor, you can store raw materials at the customer’s warehouse.","pos":[91906,91975]},{"content":"As a customer, you can postpone the actual purchase until the raw materials are required for production.","pos":[91976,92080]},{"content":"Keeping an inventory of raw materials can involve serious cost.","pos":[92083,92146]},{"content":"By using consignment inventory, a vendor can store raw materials at the customer’s warehouse.","pos":[92147,92240]},{"content":"The customer can then postpone the actual purchase until the raw materials are required for production.","pos":[92241,92344]},{"content":"Raw materials are ordered and received by using a consignment replenishment order.","pos":[92345,92427]},{"content":"This replenishment order records physical transactions but doesn’t affect the general ledger.","pos":[92428,92521]},{"content":"To distinguish between customer-owned inventory items and vendor-owned inventory items, you can use the Owner inventory dimension.","pos":[92522,92652]},{"content":"The change of ownership for inventory is handled by a journal process that handles the transfer of ownership for raw materials from the vendor-owned inventory to the customer-owned inventory.","pos":[92653,92844]},{"content":"This process triggers the creation of a purchase order and a product receipt.","pos":[92845,92922]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> This feature is limited to inbound consignment of raw materials for production.","pos":[92923,93012],"source":"**Note:** This feature is limited to inbound consignment of raw materials for production."},{"content":"It isn’t integrated with Warehouse management (WHS) and Transportation management (TMS).","pos":[93013,93101]},{"content":"As a vendor, get information about the amount of consigned inventory that is transferred to the customer.","pos":[93106,93211]},{"content":"To bill a customer, the vendor requires information about the raw materials that were purchased from the consignment inventory and the date of purchase.","pos":[93283,93435]},{"content":"The vendor can also monitor the on-hand inventory at the customer site by using the vendor collaboration interface.","pos":[93436,93551]},{"content":"Move vendor-owned inventory by using a transfer journal.","pos":[94306,94362]},{"content":"To track the physical position of the vendor-owned inventory, you must be able to record the position in the system.","pos":[94483,94599]},{"content":"By using use a transfer journal, you can record the physical movement of inventory, such as the movement from one location in a warehouse to another location in that warehouse.","pos":[94600,94776]},{"content":"Adjust vendor-owned inventory by using a counting journal.","pos":[95506,95564]},{"content":"It's important that you keep the system on-hand inventory in sync with the actual physical inventory.","pos":[95683,95784]},{"content":"The vendor-owned inventory can be adjusted in and out by using counting processes such as quantity adjustment and counting journal processes.","pos":[95785,95926]},{"content":"Find out more about consignment support in Dynamics 365 for Operations","pos":[96706,96776]},{"pos":[96883,97478],"content":"For more information about the support for consignment processes, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Consignment<ept id=\"p1\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/inventory/consignment)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Setting up consignment<ept id=\"p2\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/inventory/set-up-consignment)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>Create a consignment replenishment order (Task guide)<ept id=\"p3\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/inventory/tasks/create-consignment-replenishment-order)</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p4\">[</bpt>Change the ownership of consignment inventory based on production demand (Task guide)<ept id=\"p4\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/inventory/tasks/change-ownership-consignment)</ept>.","source":"For more information about the support for consignment processes, see [Consignment](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/inventory/consignment), [Setting up consignment](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/inventory/set-up-consignment), [Create a consignment replenishment order (Task guide)](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/inventory/tasks/create-consignment-replenishment-order), and [Change the ownership of consignment inventory based on production demand (Task guide)](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/inventory/tasks/change-ownership-consignment)."},{"pos":[97969,98029],"content":"Vendor collaboration (previously known as the Vendor portal)","linkify":"Vendor collaboration (previously known as the Vendor portal)","nodes":[{"content":"Vendor collaboration (previously known as the Vendor portal)","pos":[0,60]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[98033,98048]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[98120,98141]},{"content":"Enable vendors to respond to each purchase order line and suggest changes.","pos":[99735,99809]},{"content":"In some cases, vendors want to accept some purchase order lines but reject others.","pos":[99822,99904]},{"content":"Vendors can now individually manage purchase order lines.","pos":[99905,99962]},{"content":"Each line can be rejected, accepted, or accepted with changes.","pos":[99963,100025]},{"content":"For example, vendors can change the delivery date, split the delivery and quantity, or suggest an alternative item.","pos":[100026,100141]},{"content":"Enable vendors to manage contact person information.","pos":[100586,100638]},{"content":"Vendors can maintain contact person information for their company.","pos":[100673,100739]},{"content":"This information includes names, email addresses, and phone numbers.","pos":[100740,100808]},{"content":"Access to this feature is granted through a dedicated security role.","pos":[100809,100877]},{"content":"Share documents that are related to purchase orders with vendors.","pos":[101437,101502]},{"content":"When you must share a document with a vendor, such as a document about requirements, it’s convenient to link the document to the relevant purchase order.","pos":[101524,101677]},{"content":"The vendor can then share notes and attachments with the customer by linking the document to his or her response to the purchase order.","pos":[101678,101813]},{"content":"Document management is the underlying supporting framework, and only notes and attachments that are classified as “external” can be shared with vendors.","pos":[101814,101966]},{"content":"Provision new vendor users.","pos":[102288,102315]},{"content":"If your vendors use the vendor collaboration interface, they have a seamless way to request new user accounts when new contacts require access to vendor collaboration.","pos":[102375,102542]},{"content":"Procurement professionals can submit a request for a user account for a contact person at the vendor organization.","pos":[102543,102657]},{"content":"A vendor contact person who is already a vendor collaboration user can also submit this type of request.","pos":[102658,102762]},{"content":"This request eventually creates a new user in Dynamics 365 for Operations that has vendor-specific security roles.","pos":[102763,102877]},{"content":"It also facilitates a request to the Microsoft Azure B2B portal to provision the user with a new Azure Active Directory (Azure AD) user account.","pos":[102878,103022]},{"content":"Vendors can also request that specific vendor user accounts be inactivated, or that security roles be modified.","pos":[103023,103134]},{"content":"Find out more about support for vendor collaboration in Dynamics 365 for Operations.","pos":[103139,103223]},{"pos":[103226,103993],"content":"For more information about vendor collaboration, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Vendor collaboration with external vendors<ept id=\"p1\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/procurement/vendor-collaboration-work-external-vendors)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Vendor collaboration with customers<ept id=\"p2\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/procurement/vendor-collaboration-work-customers-dynamics-365-operations)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>Manage vendor collaboration users<ept id=\"p3\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/procurement/manage-vendor-collaboration-users)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p4\">[</bpt>Set up and maintain vendor collaboration<ept id=\"p4\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/procurement/set-up-maintain-vendor-collaboration)</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p5\">[</bpt>Vendor collaboration invoicing workspace<ept id=\"p5\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/financials/accounts-payable/vendor-portal-invoicing-workspace)</ept>.","source":"For more information about vendor collaboration, see [Vendor collaboration with external vendors](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/procurement/vendor-collaboration-work-external-vendors), [Vendor collaboration with customers](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/procurement/vendor-collaboration-work-customers-dynamics-365-operations), [Manage vendor collaboration users](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/procurement/manage-vendor-collaboration-users), [Set up and maintain vendor collaboration](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/procurement/set-up-maintain-vendor-collaboration), and [Vendor collaboration invoicing workspace](/dynamics365/unified-operations/financials/accounts-payable/vendor-portal-invoicing-workspace)."},{"pos":[104057,104086],"content":"Intercompany order processing","linkify":"Intercompany order processing","nodes":[{"content":"Intercompany order processing","pos":[0,29]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[104132,104147]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[104157,104178]},{"content":"Define, directly on sales order lines, where the demand should be sourced from, and how it should be sourced.","pos":[104228,104337]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Example<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> Create a sales order line, and specify direct delivery as the delivery type.","pos":[104338,104439],"source":"<strong>Example</strong> Create a sales order line, and specify direct delivery as the delivery type."},{"content":"The primary vendor is added to the sales order line as the sourcing point.","pos":[104440,104514]},{"content":"The flow for order taking has been improved significantly.","pos":[104524,104582]},{"content":"You can now define, directly on sales order lines, where the demand should be sourced from, and how it should be sourced.","pos":[104583,104704]},{"content":"You no longer have to wait until all lines have been added to the sales order.","pos":[104705,104783]},{"content":"New options on sales order lines let you specify the delivery type when you specify a vendor.","pos":[104784,104877]},{"content":"When you associate a vendor with sales order lines, order chains are created for delivery from the vendor.","pos":[104878,104984]},{"content":"The vendor can be an intercompany vendor that uses an internal purchase order and sales order, or it can be an external vendor that uses an external purchase order.","pos":[104994,105158]},{"content":"The delivery type can be <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Direct delivery<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Stock<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept>.","pos":[105168,105252],"source":"The delivery type can be <strong>Direct delivery</strong> or <strong>Stock</strong>."},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Stock<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> delivery type indicates that the vendor should supply to the local inventory before it ships to the customer.","pos":[105253,105389],"source":" The <strong>Stock</strong> delivery type indicates that the vendor should supply to the local inventory before it ships to the customer."},{"content":"Create an order promise directly from sales order lines.","pos":[105434,105490]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Example<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> Create a sales order line that is sourced from an intercompany vendor.","pos":[105491,105586],"source":"<strong>Example</strong> Create a sales order line that is sourced from an intercompany vendor."},{"content":"Leave the line.","pos":[105587,105602]},{"content":"Delivery dates are calculated according to availability in the sourcing company.","pos":[105603,105683]},{"content":"When you create sales order lines that use the new sourcing information, delivery dates are calculated according to the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Delivery date<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> control.","pos":[105693,105852],"source":"When you create sales order lines that use the new sourcing information, delivery dates are calculated according to the <strong>Delivery date</strong> control."},{"content":"For example, if an intercompany vendor is selected, the availability in the sourcing company is calculated.","pos":[105853,105960]},{"content":"In this way, order chains are automatically created together with sales order lines.","pos":[105961,106045]},{"content":"This functionality helps guarantee that delivery dates become visible in the sourcing company, so that the available-to-promise (ATP) profiles can handle the anticipated demands directly as sales orders are created.","pos":[106046,106261]},{"content":"Review product availability across all sourcing locations, and select the best sourcing option.","pos":[106294,106389]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Delivery alternatives<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> page has been redesigned, and now provides valuable information about all approved internal and external vendors.","pos":[106399,106555],"source":"The <strong>Delivery alternatives</strong> page has been redesigned, and now provides valuable information about all approved internal and external vendors."},{"content":"This information includes sourcing options for vendor procurement.","pos":[106556,106622]},{"content":"When you select a delivery mode, the system calculates feasible delivery dates.","pos":[106623,106702]},{"content":"You can seamlessly select the best option for the customer and apply this option to every sales order line.","pos":[106703,106810]},{"pos":[106845,106904],"content":"Warehouse enhancements for high-volume distribution centers","linkify":"Warehouse enhancements for high-volume distribution centers","nodes":[{"content":"Warehouse enhancements for high-volume distribution centers","pos":[0,59]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[106908,106923]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[106987,107008]},{"content":"Create work after goods have been packed at a packing station.","pos":[109272,109334]},{"content":"This feature is useful when there are additional processes after manual packing work (such as palletization, quality inspection, consolidation of shipments, or changes to loading docks).","pos":[109351,109537]},{"content":"The new <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Packed container picking<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> work type lets you model these tasks by using separate work lines.","pos":[109538,109641],"source":" The new **Packed container picking** work type lets you model these tasks by using separate work lines."},{"content":"You can now model packing stations to generate work after packing.","pos":[109642,109708]},{"content":"This work can be used to organize the movement of packed inventory.","pos":[109709,109776]},{"content":"Group containers at the packing station.","pos":[110454,110494]},{"content":"This feature enables multiple packages to be grouped into one container or license plate at the packing station.","pos":[110533,110645]},{"content":"For example, an e-commerce/wholesale operator can group 100 individually packed packets into a single container (such as a pallet or cage).","pos":[110646,110785]},{"content":"This container can then be moved, staged, or loaded through a single work instruction that a worker generates by scanning a single barcode (license plate) for the grouped container.","pos":[110786,110967]},{"content":"This feature minimizes the work transactions for moving many smaller packed containers.","pos":[110968,111055]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a mobile device menu item for license plate consolidation (Task guide)<ept id=\"p1\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/warehousing/tasks/create-mobile-device-license-plate-consolidation)</ept>.","pos":[111056,111275],"source":" For more information, see [Create a mobile device menu item for license plate consolidation (Task guide)](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/warehousing/tasks/create-mobile-device-license-plate-consolidation)."},{"content":"Create a release policy for packed containers.","pos":[111659,111705]},{"content":"Work that is triggered by container release can be created either automatically or manually.","pos":[111738,111830]},{"content":"When it’s automatic, work is generated at container closure by using the location directive and work template framework.","pos":[111831,111951]},{"content":"When the release is manual, the packer can decide whether the work should be generated for a single container or for a group of containers.","pos":[111952,112091]},{"content":"This feature reduces the risk that closed containers will be picked and moved before they are ready to be moved from the packing station.","pos":[112092,112229]},{"content":"It also allows for non-system-steered grouped release.","pos":[112230,112284]},{"content":"Short-picking reallocation","pos":[112841,112867]},{"content":"Support has been added for short-pick processes, to help an associate who can't pick the goods and wants to fulfil the order when the item that is required is available at another location.","pos":[112920,113109]},{"content":"You can use an automatic reallocation process that uses the same location directives to retrieve the goods if they are available at another location.","pos":[113110,113259]},{"content":"Alternatively, when manual reallocation is used, the mobile device show a list of locations together with the available quantity.","pos":[113260,113389]},{"content":"The warehouse worker can then select which location to use inventory from.","pos":[113390,113464]},{"content":"These two methods can be set individually or combined as a single command on the warehouse worker menu.","pos":[113465,113568]},{"content":"When manual re-allocation is used, the warehouse worker can pick the short-picked item quantity from several locations.","pos":[113569,113688]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Set up short picking item reallocation (Task guide)<ept id=\"p1\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/warehousing/tasks/set-up-short-picking-item-reallocation)</ept>.","pos":[113689,113872],"source":" For more information, see [Set up short picking item reallocation (Task guide)](/dynamics365/unified-operations/supply-chain/warehousing/tasks/set-up-short-picking-item-reallocation)."},{"content":"Move inventory that has work associated with it.","pos":[114062,114110]},{"content":"You can now move inventory that has work associated with it.","pos":[114141,114201]},{"content":"This feature can be useful if, for example, a worker wants to clear some inbound dock space and move registered pallets that are waiting to be put away to another inbound location.","pos":[114202,114382]},{"content":"The dock is cleared and can receive an additional load of goods, and the inventory that has been moved is updated with new put-away information.","pos":[114383,114527]},{"content":"This feature can also be used to free up space at picking locations by moving the inventory that has work associated with it and creating space for replenishment.","pos":[114528,114690]},{"content":"You can also use it to move loads from one staging location to another without losing the loading work that has been generated.","pos":[114691,114818]},{"content":"In this way, the feature can help optimize the time that is required to load trucks when they arrive.","pos":[114819,114920]},{"content":"You can move inventory that has been reserved for sales orders, transfer order issues, transfer order receipts, and purchase orders.","pos":[114921,115053]},{"content":"Movement is prevented if it will cause lines to be split.","pos":[115054,115111]},{"content":"For example, if you have a work line for 100 pieces of an item, you can't move only 30 pieces of that item to another location.","pos":[115112,115239]},{"content":"Merge license plates that have work associated with them.","pos":[115244,115301]},{"content":"You can merge license plates that have outbound work associated with them.","pos":[115323,115397]},{"content":"For example, when a pick has been broken into several pieces of work, it can be useful to allow the license plates to be merged after they are delivered at the staging location.","pos":[115398,115575]},{"content":"License plates can be consolidated only if they are at the same location, are members of the same load, and have the same shipment information.","pos":[115576,115719]},{"content":"Freeze picking work that is associated with replenishment at the line level.","pos":[116426,116502]},{"content":"You can now freeze work at the line level instead of at the header level, so that workers can fulfil pick lines that aren’t frozen by demand replenishment.","pos":[116505,116660]},{"content":"Therefore, a wholesaler that has large sales orders, or a retailer that has large sales orders or replenishment transfer orders, can allow the picking work to start on all lines that aren't subject to replenishment work.","pos":[116661,116881]},{"content":"The picking and replenishment work can then be completed in parallel.","pos":[116882,116951]},{"content":"This feature can be configured so that you can select whether to freeze at the header level or the line level.","pos":[116952,117062]},{"content":"You can also use both methods and create a work template for each method.","pos":[117063,117136]},{"content":"The header/line configuration is set on work templates, but you can change it directly on the generated work.","pos":[117137,117246]},{"content":"Cancel work by using the mobile device.","pos":[117608,117647]},{"content":"You can now cancel work by using the mobile device, with or without demand replenishment.","pos":[117687,117776]},{"content":"Previously, you had to use the rich client.","pos":[117777,117820]},{"content":"To enable this functionality, create a mobile device menu item that has the mode set to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Indirect<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and the activity code set to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Cancel work<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[117821,117967],"source":" To enable this functionality, create a mobile device menu item that has the mode set to **Indirect** and the activity code set to **Cancel work**."},{"pos":[118793,118825],"content":"Warehouse operation enhancements","linkify":"Warehouse operation enhancements","nodes":[{"content":"Warehouse operation enhancements","pos":[0,32]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[118829,118844]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[118866,118887]},{"content":"Model different container types.","pos":[121885,121917]},{"content":"You might use different container types in the warehouse to optimize storage and for other reasons.","pos":[121922,122021]},{"content":"The new Container type entity has the physical characteristics of the container types.","pos":[122022,122108]},{"content":"You can now associate license plates with a specific container type and use location stocking limits.","pos":[122109,122210]},{"content":"For example, you can use this feature to control how many pallets (or other container types) you allow at a specific location.","pos":[122211,122337]},{"content":"Container types have also been added to unit sequence groups to add default container types for the receiving process.","pos":[122338,122456]},{"content":"Container types can be used with inbound and outbound location directives.","pos":[122457,122531]},{"content":"They can also be used in the on-hand inventory view to help you determine how many container types are currently stored on hand.","pos":[122532,122660]},{"content":"For more information, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Use of license plates associated with a container type to drive warehouse management processes<ept id=\"p1\">](https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/dynamicsaxscm/2016/06/20/use-of-license-plates-associated-with-a-container-type-to-drive-warehouse-management-processes/)</ept> blog post.","pos":[122661,122953],"source":" For more information, see the [Use of license plates associated with a container type to drive warehouse management processes](https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/dynamicsaxscm/2016/06/20/use-of-license-plates-associated-with-a-container-type-to-drive-warehouse-management-processes/) blog post."},{"content":"Although this blog post describes an update to Microsoft Dynamics AX 2012, the same support has now been added to Dynamics 365 for Operations.","pos":[122954,123096]},{"content":"Reverse shipments.","pos":[123413,123431]},{"content":"In a warehouse, you must be able to handle late changes.","pos":[123450,123506]},{"content":"For example, some goods might be damaged, so that you can't ship them.","pos":[123507,123577]},{"content":"Alternatively, a customer might make a late request to cancel or change an order.","pos":[123578,123659]},{"content":"Dynamics 365 for Operations now lets you reverse a shipment.","pos":[123660,123720]},{"content":"Therefore, you can cancel a packing slip so that you can update it with the correct quantities later.","pos":[123721,123822]},{"content":"Similarly, on the inbound flow, you can cancel product receipts so that an updated version can be created.","pos":[123823,123929]},{"content":"Use pallets that have mixed items.","pos":[124941,124975]},{"content":"You can now receive and register a “mixed” pallet.","pos":[124978,125028]},{"content":"A mixed pallet consists of different items that are assembled onto one pallet for one or several purchase orders or lines.","pos":[125029,125151]},{"content":"All registrations can be summarized into one target license plate.","pos":[125152,125218]},{"content":"This process is enabled though the warehouse mobile device.","pos":[125219,125278]},{"content":"For example, when the pallet of mixed items arrives at the warehouse, the receiving clerk identifies the items and the quantities on the pallet before the pallet is moved to dedicated put-away locations.","pos":[125279,125482]},{"content":"The put-away locations are identified by work templates and location directives.","pos":[125483,125563]},{"content":"If the put-away locations are spread over several items that have fixed locations, this feature creates as many put work lines as there are different items on the mixed pallet.","pos":[125564,125740]},{"content":"This feature makes registration and put-away of the received mixed items pallets faster and more flexible.","pos":[125741,125847]},{"content":"For more information, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Receive and register a pallet with mixed source document lines using one license plate<ept id=\"p1\">](https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/dynamicsaxscm/2016/05/13/receive-and-register-a-pallet-with-mixed-source-document-lines-using-1-license-plate-purchase-order-matching/)</ept> blog pot and the information about mixed pallet support in the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>announcement of our recent cumulative update<ept id=\"p2\">](https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/dynamicsaxscm/2016/06/30/whats-new-in-cu11-for-wms-and-tms/)</ept>.","pos":[125848,126340],"source":" For more information, see the [Receive and register a pallet with mixed source document lines using one license plate](https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/dynamicsaxscm/2016/05/13/receive-and-register-a-pallet-with-mixed-source-document-lines-using-1-license-plate-purchase-order-matching/) blog pot and the information about mixed pallet support in the [announcement of our recent cumulative update](https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/dynamicsaxscm/2016/06/30/whats-new-in-cu11-for-wms-and-tms/)."},{"content":"Although this blog post describes an update to AX 2012, the same support has now been added to Dynamics 365 for Operations.","pos":[126341,126464]},{"pos":[126472,126525],"content":"Minor feature enhancements in Supply chain management","linkify":"Minor feature enhancements in Supply chain management","nodes":[{"content":"Minor feature enhancements in Supply chain management","pos":[0,53]}]},{"content":"What you can do","pos":[126571,126586]},{"content":"Why this is important","pos":[126596,126617]},{"content":"Use new data entities to import and export data.","pos":[126667,126715]},{"content":"You can import and export data by using these data entities:","pos":[126725,126785],"source":"You can import and export data by using these data entities:\n"},{"content":"Freight invoice","pos":[126795,126810]},{"content":"Aggregate on-hand by warehouse and inventory status","pos":[126820,126871]},{"content":"Inventory charges","pos":[126881,126898]},{"content":"Quotation","pos":[126908,126917]},{"content":"Use the enhanced Gantt control to develop interactive scheduling scenarios.","pos":[126962,127037]},{"content":"The enhanced Gantt control lets you develop new interactive scheduling scenarios and deliver enhanced APIs that can be used to customize the appearance of activities.","pos":[127047,127213]},{"content":"Here are some of the new APIs:","pos":[127214,127244],"source":" Here are some of the new APIs:\n"},{"content":"Vertical drag-and-drop of activities","pos":[127254,127290]},{"content":"Add/remove activities","pos":[127300,127321]},{"content":"Preview booked periods in summary bar","pos":[127331,127368]},{"content":"Change color and style of activity borders","pos":[127378,127420]},{"content":"Change color, style, and background of text in grid","pos":[127430,127481]},{"content":"Better handle material and resource planning.","pos":[127525,127570]},{"content":"A few enhancements have been made to material and resource planning:","pos":[127580,127648],"source":"A few enhancements have been made to material and resource planning:\n"},{"content":"The issue margin is now handled when an item is on hand.","pos":[127658,127714]},{"content":"Overwrite the delivery date when you firm planned orders.","pos":[127724,127781]},{"content":"Prioritize fulfillment of orders over safety stock.","pos":[127791,127842]},{"content":"Prevent scheduling of planned orders in the past.","pos":[127852,127901]},{"content":"Report actual consumption for production, and view inventory status.","pos":[127946,128014]},{"content":"You can view actual consumption for production.","pos":[128024,128071]},{"content":"Additionally, a new <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Display inventory status<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> check box that has been added to <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Movement<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> on the <bpt id=\"p3\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Work creation<ept id=\"p3\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> menu item lets you view inventory status.","pos":[128072,128272],"source":" Additionally, a new <strong>Display inventory status</strong> check box that has been added to <strong>Movement</strong> on the <strong>Work creation</strong> menu item lets you view inventory status."},{"content":"Calculate volumetric weight, if the rates for your shipping carrier are based on volumetric weight.","pos":[128305,128404]},{"content":"A new TMS rate engine that is based on volumetric weight has been added, so that you can calculate volumetric weight.","pos":[128414,128531]},{"pos":[128564,128572],"content":"See also","linkify":"See also","nodes":[{"content":"See also","pos":[0,8]}]},{"pos":[128583,128628],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>What's new or changed<ept id=\"p1\">](whats-new-changed.md)</ept>","source":"[What's new or changed](whats-new-changed.md)"}]}